法規內容.條文內容:
Specialties of nurse practitioner are as follows:
(1) Internal medicine;
(2) Surgery

The contents of the written test stipulated in the preceding article are as follows:
(1) General principles of specialty nursing: including the role and responsibilities of nurse practitioner, nursing ethics, medical regulations and quality management of health promotion;
(2) Advanced specialty nursing: including advanced pharmacology, advanced physiological pathology, advanced health assessment, as well as diagnosis and treatment of health problems.

Candidates registering for specialty examinations shall present a photocopy of their professional registered nurse certificates and any of the following supporting documents:
(1) Photocopies of certificates for having engaged in clinical nursing work in the fields related to the specialties stipulated in Article 3 for three years or more and for completing subsequent training for nurse practitioners;
(2) Photocopies of certificates of nurse practitioner issued by countries whose nurse practitioner system is equivalent to that of our country, as determined by the central authorities;
(3) Photocopies of certificates for receiving the training instructed by nurse practitioners in internal medicine or surgery accredited by the central authorities and for completing the additional courses specified in Appendix 2.
For those who completed the nurse practitioner training before the Regulations were amended and came into force on February 25, 2011, the regulations before amendment shall apply regarding their proof of clinical practice.

Candidates passing the specialty examinations may apply to the central authorities for issuance of the nurse practitioner certificate.
The following particulars shall be indicated on the said certificate:
(1) Specialty;
(2) Certificate number;
(3) Name and gender;
(4) ID number;
(5) Date of birth;
(6) Period of validity;
(7) Date issued

Nurse practitioners shall take the following continuing education courses every six years with cumulative points of 180 or above:
(1) Professional courses related to specialty nursing;
(2) Quality courses related to specialty nursing;
(3) Medical ethics;
(4) Medical laws and regulations;
The cumulative points of continuing education courses in Subparagraphs 3 and 4 of the preceding paragraph shall include at least 18 points from infection control and gender issues-related courses. No more points will be counted when 36 points have been gained from such courses.
